@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "";
}
<h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <style>
        .title-gradient {
            background: linear-gradient(to right, #0033ff, #0099ff);
            -webkit-background-clip: text;
            -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
        }
    </style>
    <title>Privacy Policy</title>
</head>
<body>
    <h1><span class="title-gradient">Privacy Policy</span></h1>
    <p>
        Effective Date: [09.19.2023]
    </p>
    <p>
        This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and protect personal information during your visit and interaction with our website and the use of our services. We understand the importance of privacy and are committed to protecting your personal information. By using our website, you agree to the practices described in this Privacy Policy.
    </p>
    <h2>1. Information We Collect:</h2>
    <p>
        <strong>1.1 Personal Information:</strong><br>
        We may collect personal information such as your name, email address, contact information, and any other information you voluntarily provide to us during your interaction with our website or use of our services.
    </p>
    <p>
        <strong>1.2 Non-Personal Information:</strong><br>
        We may also collect non-personal information, including but not limited to your IP address, browser type, operating system, and other technical information when you visit our website. This information is used for trend analysis, site administration, user traffic tracking, and the collection of demographic information for general use.
    </p>
    <h2>2. Use of Information:</h2>
    <p>
        <strong>2.1 Personal Information:</strong><br>
        We use the collected personal information to provide and improve our services, respond to your inquiries, communicate with you, send you relevant information or updates, and for other legitimate business purposes. We may also use your personal information for marketing purposes, but only with your consent.
    </p>
    <p>
        <strong>2.2 Non-Personal Information:</strong><br>
        Non-personal information is used for website usage trend analysis, site administration, improvement of our services, and the collection of demographic information. This information may be shared with third parties for these purposes.
    </p>
    <h2>3. Data Retention:</h2>
    <p>
        We will retain your personal information for as long as necessary to achieve the purposes outlined in this Privacy Policy unless the law requires or allows a longer retention period.
    </p>
    <h2>4. Information Disclosure:</h2>
    <p>
        We may disclose your personal information to third parties only in the following cases:
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>With your consent or at your direction.</li>
        <li>With service providers or partners who assist us in operating our website or providing services, provided that they agree to maintain the confidentiality of your information.</li>
        <li>As required by law, such as complying with a court order or similar legal process.</li>
        <li>In connection with a merger, acquisition, or sale of all or part of our assets as permitted by law.</li>
    </ul>
    <h2>5. Security:</h2>
    <p>
        We take reasonable measures to protect your personal information from unauthorized access, disclosure, alteration, or destruction. However, there is no absolutely secure method for transmitting information over the Internet or electronic storage, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.
    </p>
    <h2>6. Links to Third-Party Resources:</h2>
    <p>
        Our website may contain links to third-party websites that are not owned or controlled by us. We are not responsible for the privacy practices or content of such third-party websites. We recommend reviewing the privacy policy of these websites before providing any personal information.
    </p>
    <h2>7. Children's Privacy:</h2>
    <p>
        Our services are not intended for individuals under the age of 18. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children. If we discover that we have received personal information from a person under the age of 18 without the consent of parents or guardians, we will take steps to remove this information from our servers.
    </p>
    <h2>8. Changes to Privacy Policy:</h2>
    <p>
        We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We recommend periodically reviewing this page for updates. Changes to this Privacy Policy become effective upon publication on this page.
    </p>
    <h2>9. Contact Us:</h2>
    <p>
        If you have any questions or concerns regarding this Privacy Policy, please contact us using the contact information provided on our website.
    </p>
</body>
</html>
